.SH NAME
epf_ntb_config_spad_bar_free \- Free the physical memory associated with config + scratchpad region
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" epf_ntb_config_spad_bar_free
.BI "(struct epf_ntb *ntb "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ntb" 12
NTB device that facilitates communication between HOST1 and HOST2
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
+-----------------+------->+------------------+        +-----------------+
|       BAR0      |        |  CONFIG REGION   |        |       BAR0      |
+-----------------+----+   +------------------+<-------+-----------------+
|       BAR1      |    |   |SCRATCHPAD REGION |        |       BAR1      |
+-----------------+    +-->+------------------+<-------+-----------------+
|       BAR2      |            Local Memory            |       BAR2      |
+-----------------+                                    +-----------------+
|       BAR3      |                                    |       BAR3      |
+-----------------+                                    +-----------------+
|       BAR4      |                                    |       BAR4      |
+-----------------+                                    +-----------------+
|       BAR5      |                                    |       BAR5      |
+-----------------+                                    +-----------------+
EP CONTROLLER 1                                        EP CONTROLLER 2

Free the Local Memory mentioned in the above diagram. After invoking this
function, any of config + self scratchpad region of HOST1 or peer scratchpad
region of HOST2 should not be accessed.
